  <section id="luis" class="team-member <%= @member != 'luis' ? 'hidden' : '' %>">
    <div class="wrapper">
      <h1>Luís Zamith</h1>
      <h2>Backend Developer</h2>

      <p>A geek at heart. Got in touch with Web development while finishing his graduation and since then, he has never stopped loving it and is constantly trying to learn more.</p>
      <p>Luckily, he found a group of people who shared the same passion for building reliable and beautiful products, and with whom he co-founded Group Buddies.</p>
      <p>Apart from Web development, another great passion of his is doing sports. He plays basketball almost daily and goes skiing whenever he can.</p>

      <a href="#" class="left arrow"></a>
      <a href="#" class="right arrow"></a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="miguel" class="team-member <%= @member != 'miguel' ? 'hidden' : '' %>">
    <div class="wrapper">
      <h1>Miguel Regedor</h1>
      <h2>Technical Advisor</h2>

      <p>Started hacking walkie-talkies and dismantling computers at an early age. A few years later, he began learning Pascal, C, Delphi and Visual Basic.</p>
      <p>Thanks to his expertise in the Rails framework, he moved to England and New York. Two years later, he came back to Portugal where he co-founded Group Buddies with the rest of the team.</p>
      <p>In 2012, he left his role as CEO and moved to Germany to work at Pro7, the country's biggest private TV channel. He still maintains a strong connection with Group Buddies as a Technical Advisor.</p>

      <a href="#" class="left arrow"></a>
      <a href="#" class="right arrow"></a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="pedro" class="team-member <%= @member != 'pedro' ? 'hidden' : '' %>">
